definition.value: A carious tooth lesion that is either wholly or partially part of the tooth root.
A tooth disorder that is not formed by tooth decay.
A non-carious tooth lesion that is the result of functional or parafunctional activity of the jaws or a process of friction or an abrasive process
A process during which the surface of the tooth is cleaned.
A tooth cleaning process during which an object is used to clean the tooth (or teeth) by applying a powder, paste, or liquid (i.e., dentifrice).

value.value: A bruxism that occurs during sleep and is characterised by rhythmic (phasic) or non-rhythmic (tonic) movements of the jaw.

definition.value: A tooth disorder that is an outcome of a ruture or break of some part of the tooth.
A prosthesis that forms the part of a prosthetic tooth  that is in direct contact with the bone and actually provides the fixation to the bone.
A prosthesis that forms the part of a prosthetic tooth to which the restoration is attached and supports the restoration.
A prosthesis that forms the part of a prosthetic tooth which provides the prosthetic tooth with the functionallity and appearance of a natural tooth.
A prosthesis that is permanently attached attached to some part of the mouth.
A process during which the tooth is affected by an abrasive material.
A dental implant body fabricated to fit the supporting areas of mandible or maxilla with permucosal extensions for support and attachment of abutments.
A material entity of a certain hardness and density that helps remove material from the surface of an entity.
A dental implant body that is less that 3mm in diameter.
An endodontic restorative procedure during which material is placed over exposed or nearly dental pulp in order to protect and promote healing of the dental pulp.

value.value: A bruxism that occurs during wakeful-ness and is characterised by repetitive or sustained tooth contact and/or by bracing or thrusting of the mandible.

definition.value: A surgical endodontic procedure during which medications are placed inside the pulp chamber in order to induce the formation of living replacement tissue.
A mechnical tooth lesion that formed as a result of some friction process.
A removable partial denture procedure in which the prosthesis being constructed or fitted replaces some but not all of the patient's maxillary teeth.
A removable partial denture procedure in which the prosthesis being constructed or fitted replaces some but not all of the patient's mandibular teeth.
A dental implant body that is placed in the mouth for short duration of time in order to allow adequate time for healing or completion of definitive treatment planning.
A dental implant crown constructed out of ceramic.

label.value: porcelain fused to metal impant crown

definition.value: A fixed prosthodontics procedure during which an artificial crown is attached to an dental implant abutment.

label.value: ceramic dental implant crown attachement procedure

definition.value: A dental implant crown attachment procedure in which the implant crown is composed of ceramic.

label.value: porcelain fused to metal dental implant crown attachement procedure

definition.value: A dental implant crown attachment procedure in which the implant crown is composed of porcelain fused to metal.
A fixed prosthodontics procedure during which an abutment is attached to an implant body.

label.value: dental implant retainer attachement procedure for fixed partial denture

definition.value: A dental implant abutment attachment procedure during which a retainer for a fixed partial denture is attached to an implant body.
a processed material that bears a prothetic role
a prosthesis that has been fabricated for use as a substitute for a natural tooth
A tooth restoration procedure in which the dental restoration material is placed in the tooth via some direct dental restoration material combination process.
A tooth restoration procedure in which the dental restoration material is placed in the tooth via some dental material tooth attachment process.
A crown restoration procedure in which 3 of the 4 surfaces on an anterior tooth is restored. The dental restoration material extends to (or almost to) the gum line.
A dental material combination process in which one or more materials forms a substructure and then one or more materials are fused (or baked) onto this substructure.
A tooth that is either an incisor or a canine.
A tooth that is either a molar or premolar.

label.value: dental implant retainer attachement procedure for ceramic fixed partial denture

definition.value: A dental implant retainer attachement procedure for fixed partial denture in which the retainer being attached to the implant body is to be used as a retainer for a ceramic fixed partial denture.
a prosthesis that replaces one or more, but less than all, of the natural teeth and associated structures
A fixed partial denture that is suppored and retained by underlying tissue and some or all of the remaining teeth.
A partial denture that is permanently attached to prepared natural teeth, roots, or implants.
A material to be added role that inheres in a material entity that replaces some missing body part.
A prosthetic role that is realized by activities in which the material entity (bearing the role) is used a manner that is similar to how the body part that the prosthesis replaces would be used.

label.value: prosthetic right upper third secondary molar tooth

definition.value: A prosthetic tooth that is used a substitute for a right upper third secondary molar tooth (tooth 1).

label.value: prosthetic right upper second secondary molar tooth

definition.value: A prosthetic tooth that is used a substitute for a right upper second secondary molar tooth (tooth 2).

label.value: prosthetic right upper first secondary molar tooth

definition.value: A prosthetic tooth that is used a substitute for a right upper first secondary molar tooth (tooth 3).

label.value: prosthetic right upper second secondary premolar tooth

definition.value: A prosthetic tooth that is used a substitute for a right upper second secondary premolar tooth (tooth 4).

label.value: prosthetic right upper first secondary premolar tooth

definition.value: A prosthetic tooth that is used a substitute for a right upper first secondary premolar tooth (tooth 5).
